coupled_prompt_600:
CosmoCaixa Barcelona is a free program that allows the public to create and publish information about Barcelona in Spanish. The purpose of this web site is to help readers learn more about this famous city and its culture.

The Spanish edition of the magazine has been published since 1986. It covers subjects related to the capital city of Catalonia, from tourism, cuisine, architecture, cultural heritage, art, sports and many others. As the program goes on, new topics are added to the web site.

CosmoCaixa is a non-profit project organized by the Center for Urban Studies of the National University of Catalonia (UNUC). A member of the Instituto Catalánico de Estudios Sociales (ICES), we conduct research on public policies, social problems, and urban development. Our research aims at increasing the understanding of the local social structures by presenting them in a way accessible to people.

Please make sure you link to this page from your web site or blog. Thank you for your cooperation.

If you would like to contribute something to this website, please contact the webmasters at cosmociaixabarcelona@gmail.com with "contribution" in the subject line. We will do our best to implement it.

The content will be updated as often as possible, but only after checking with the contributors to make sure that everything they have prepared is done correctly.
